            &lt;Delete basePath=&quot;${sys:storm.home}/logs/&quot; maxDepth=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
              &lt;IfFileName glob=&quot;*.service.????????&quot; /&gt;
              &lt;IfLastModified age=&quot;4d&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/Delete&gt;
          &lt;/DefaultRolloverStrategy&gt;
     . . .

    &lt;RollingFile&gt;

Finally, be careful! There is no way to recover files deleted this way. :-)


  [1]: http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/appenders.html#CustomDeleteOnRollover
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/FileSystem.html#getPathMatcher(java.lang.String)
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/regex/Pattern.html
